_README.title: Whale Events - Filtered Chart Data Export
_README.description: This file contains order book events and price data filtered according to your selected criteria.
_README.data_source: MEXC Futures WebSocket API - Level 2 (L2) Order Book Data
important_notes: L2 data is AGGREGATED by price level - individual orders not visible
Increase/Decrease events are AMBIGUOUS - cannot distinguish fills from cancellations
Market Buy/Sell events are DEFINITIVE - we see actual trade executions
USD values are NOTIONAL (futures contracts with leverage) - not actual capital spent
All timestamps are in ISO 8601 format (UTC)
Filters were active during export - this is NOT the complete dataset
_README.full_documentation: See WHALE_EVENTS_EXPLAINED.md for complete technical explanation

filter_summary.note: Only events matching ALL active filters are included in this export

market_buy.name: Market Buy
market_buy.description: Aggressive buyer executed at ask price immediately. Cannot be cancelled (already filled).
market_buy.market_impact: Bullish - buyer willing to pay premium to execute NOW
market_buy.what_happened: Someone bought contracts at the ask price, removing liquidity from sellers

market_sell.name: Market Sell
market_sell.description: Aggressive seller executed at bid price immediately. Cannot be cancelled (already filled).
market_sell.market_impact: Bearish - seller willing to take discount to execute NOW
market_sell.what_happened: Someone sold contracts at the bid price, removing liquidity from buyers

field_definitions.price: Price level where event occurred (execution price for market orders, resting price for limit orders)
field_definitions.volume: Contracts quantity. For increase/decrease: this is the CHANGE amount, not total. See 'info' field for new total.
field_definitions.usd_value: Notional value = price Ã— volume. For futures: represents total exposure, not actual margin required.
field_definitions.distance_from_mid_pct: Distance from mid-price as percentage. Negative = below mid (bid side), Positive = above mid (ask side)
field_definitions.level: Position in order book depth. 1 = best bid/ask (closest to market), higher = further from market
field_definitions.order_count: Number of separate orders at this price level (L2 limitation: cannot see individual order sizes)
field_definitions.side: bid = buy orders, ask = sell orders, buy/sell = market order direction
field_definitions.event_type: See event_type_explanations section for detailed description of each type
field_definitions.info: Additional context (e.g., 'total:75000' shows new total volume after increase/decrease)
